!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

substance /ˈsʌbstəns/

(substances) 

1. N-COUNT A substance is a solid, powder, liquid, or gas with particular properties. 物质 

例： There's absolutely no regulation of cigarettes to make sure that they don't include poisonous substances. 绝对没有确保香烟不含有毒物质的规定。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Substance is the quality of being important or significant. 实质 [正式] 

例： It's questionable whether anything of substance has been achieved. 是否已取得任何实质性的进展值得质疑。 

3. N-SING The substance of what someone says or writes is the main thing that they are trying to say. 要旨 

例： The substance of his discussions doesn't really matter. 他讨论的要旨实际并不重要。 

4. N-UNCOUNT If you say that something has no substance , you mean that it is not true. 正确性 [正式] 

例： There is no substance in any of these allegations. 这些指控没有一个是正确的。

</div>

